This is a must read commentary. The url it is on is "f.uckthesouth.com". Just take out the first "." and type in what remains as a url. You know..."fu--thesouth.com". 
 
 
 It is a bit drastic but entertaining none the less.

The problem with the whole thing is that it assumes that everyone (or at least a large majority) of people in these "red" states are actually red (ironic that being a republican is "RED").
 
 A few states are over 60/40 "red" but most of states are one color or another by a pretty slim margin (with the exceptions of places like Kansas or New York).
 And I'm saying that a 6-8% margin is relatively slim, especially if we are going to talk in extremes like all red and all blue, like the webpage says.
